data.meta_description: This is a list of English voice actors in Eiyuden Chronicle: Hundred Heroes. The first English-language voice actors revealed were Andrew Wheildon-Dennis as Nowa, Will de Renzy-Martin as Seign Kesling, and Kimberly Woods as Marisa, in the September 21, 2023 pre-order trailer[1].
data.text:
This is a list of English voice actors in Eiyuden Chronicle: Hundred Heroes. The first English-language voice actors revealed were Andrew Wheildon-Dennis as Nowa, Will de Renzy-Martin as Seign Kesling, and Kimberly Woods as Marisa, in the September 21, 2023 pre-order trailer[1].

Overall, some 72 individual English-language voice actors are credited in Eiyuden Chronicle: Hundred Heroes. Voice acting was done under PitStop Productions with Pitstop's Beth Park serving as lead voice and casting director for the English-language dub of the game[2]. As such, most of the English-language roles in Eiyuden Chronicle: Hundred Heroes are voiced by British or British-residing actors.

The shared production agency also means that many of the actors have been cast in the same games, such as Baldur's Gate III, Dragon's Dogma II, and various Warhammer franchise games, among others.
